node.text:
Entrepreneurship can be a Lonely Road 🗺 

Day in Day out working on your business. Often times only person you can depend on to get it done... is you. 

Sacrificed relationships, time with family & friends, holidays, events, etc. I’ve missed so much these past few years while I kept my head down to focus on my businesses. It’s not easy. It’s not supposed to be ❌

Learn to surround yourself with entrepreneurs or like minded individuals. Best advice I could give to someone starting out. It’s lonely starting out. Find people you vibe with, connect with, can work with and enjoy being around. It’s key! 🔑 

My boys @michelsonrenard & @alex__renard I met around this time last year. Crazy to think it’s been about a year now. Time flies ⏰ 

Be ready to go through some sh*t starting out. Hell even years in. But with the right people around you... any task seems easy. Grateful for the people I have around me. Y’all know who you are 🤍

Just because you’re growing doesn’t mean the people in your life are growing with you...⁣⁣

God places people in our lives for seasons. It’s rare you find those people that have truly good intentions and are there for life-long relationships. ⁣⁣

Focus on YOU ⁣⁣
Strive to be the BEST VERSION of YOU every single day. ⁣⁣
And remember... ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
You’re supposed to change. Your supposed to grow and it’s NOT supposed to be easy BUT it is NECESSARY! ⁣⁣
———⁣⁣
Go crush it this Friday y’all! 💯
